<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-18T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-18T09:00:00-05:00" n="96" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/8–1845: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-18T16:00:00+02:00">August 18,
                                    1945—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 7:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>5003. Bidault told me last night orally that the French Govt was
                            agreeable to the Tripartite action mentioned in paragraph 4 Dept’s 3754,
                            August 9, 1 p.m.<note n="93" xml:id="d96fn93">Same as telegram 6704 on
                                same date to London, <ref target="#pg_134">p. 134</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>